# --
* Localization

This software uses boost::locale for localization.

A Python script is provided to generate a localization template, extract translatable strings from the source code, and update portable object (.po) translation dictionaries.

For example, to create or update a German dictionary, run

#+BEGIN_SRC sh
\$ ./tools/i18ngen --locale de_DE
#+END_SRC

The resulting ~de_DE.po~ file can then be edited to add or change German translations.

For more information, run

#+BEGIN_SRC sh
\$ ./tools/i18ngen -h
#+END_SRC

#+BEGIN_VERSE
*Note:*
[[https://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/][GNU gettext utilities]] are required for generating localized dictionaries.
#+END_VERSE

